author: Bani McSpedden
title: Does Apple's silence on Apple Watch sales signal failure?
text:
Communications minister Malcolm Turnbull is one prominent Australian who has purchased an Apple Watch. Andrew Meares In a post-results conference Cook said it wasn't right to compare Apple Watch growth as part of the year-over-year or sequential increase in Apple's "other revenue" category, because other categories, such as iPad, were decelerating.
He said sales of Apple Watch exceeded internal expectations, despite supply trailing demand, and the failure to give figures was in order to deny competitors having the information.
He added that Apple Watch sales were higher in June than April or May and he expected it to be a popular gift in the fourth quarter.
Bani McSpedden is watch editor of watch-next and The Australian financial Review .
